.SH "NAME"
Test2::Formatter::Stream \- Test2 Formatter that directly writes events.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
.IX Header "DESCRIPTION"
This formatter writes all test2 events to event files (one per process/thread)
instead of writing them to \s-1STDERR/STDOUT.\s0 It will output synchronization
messages to \s-1STDERR/STDOUT\s0 every time an event is written. From this data the
test output can be properly reconstructed in order with \s-1STDERR/STDOUT\s0 and
events mostly synced so that they appear in the correct order.
.PP
This formatter is not usually useful to humans. This formatter is used by
Test2::Harness when possible to prevent the loss of data that normally
occurs when \s-1TAP\s0 is used.
.SH "SYNOPSIS"
.IX Header "SYNOPSIS"
If you really want your test to output this:
.PP
.Vb 3
\&    use Test2::Formatter::Stream;
\&    use Test2::V0;
\&    ...
.Ve
.PP
Otherwise just use App::Yath without the \f(CW\*(C`\-\-no\-stream\*(C'\fR argument and this
formatter will be used when possible.
